// Match-arm equality on a mistyped scrutinee must not emit invalid
// IR. Fuzz found this in v3.1.0: annotating a List literal as `Map`
// makes the for-loop variable a String*, then `n: Int := x` keeps
// the binding pointer-shaped while the match's `case 3` literal is
// an i32. The struct-eq path then tried to bitcast i32 → String*,
// which LLVM rejected as malformed IR. Fix: when R is a primitive
// and L is a struct ptr, return constant-false instead of forging
// an impossible bitcast — the arm can't match at runtime anyway.
//
// Probe passes when the compiler does NOT report "malformed IR" or
// "Internal compiler error". The program's runtime behavior is
// undefined (it's mistyped), but it must not crash the compiler.

define main() -> void {
    items: Map = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
    for x in items {
        n: Int := x
        match n {
            case 3 { print("three") }
            case 5 { print("five") }
        }
    }
    print("ok")
}
